        'A starter set in the right length range matters more than the brand.',
        'Used clubs are common and fine. The right length is everything.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Glove', body: [
        'Sized by hand circumference. The glove goes on the lead hand (left for right-handed players).',
        'Should fit snug, no bunching at the palm.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Shoes', body: [
        'Spikeless golf shoes for kids. Simpler, more versatile, kinder on the parking lot.',
        'A regular athletic shoe works at first. Spikes only when the kid is consistent enough to need them.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
  crew: {
    intro: 'Most crew gear is club-provided. The fit decisions are uniform layer and cold-weather kit.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Unisuit', body: [
        'The team usually selects the brand and color.',
        'Sizing runs snug. A loose unisuit catches on the seat and the rigger.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Layers', body: [
        'Compression base layer for spring practice.',
        'Windbreaker shell for cold or wet conditions. Hood preferred.',
        'A pair of socks dedicated to crew. They wear out fast in the boat.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Sunglasses', body: [
        'With a strap or retainer. Glare off water is intense.',
        'Sunscreen is also gear at this level. SPF 50.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
  'martial-arts': {
    intro: 'The gi is the only thing parents typically buy outside the school. Sizing is by height and weight, not by age.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Gi (uniform)', body: [
        'Karate and taekwondo: lightweight, sized by height in inches.',
        'BJJ: heavier weave, sized 0-A6. The school will tell you what they require.',
        'Two gis is the right number. Practices fill the laundry hamper fast.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Belt', body: [
        'Comes from the school. Length should wrap twice around the waist with about a foot of tail on each side.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Mouthguard and protection', body: [
        'Required for sparring in most styles.',
        'Headgear, chest protectors, shin guards: usually sized by age and provided by the school for the first six months.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
  gymnastics: {
    intro: 'The gym provides the apparatus. The kid needs leotards, grips at higher levels, and a few small accessories.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Leotards', body: [
        'Sized child small through adult medium. The brand chart is the source of truth.',
        'Three to four leotards is the working set. Chlorinated pools and chalk dust shorten their life.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Grips', body: [
        'Bars only. Level 4 or 5 is when most gyms introduce grips.',
        'Sized by hand width. The gym\'s coach will help. Do not buy unprompted.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Hair', body: [
        'A small pouch with hair ties, bobby pins, gel, and a small hairbrush. Lives in the bag.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
  cheer: {
    intro: 'Most cheer kit is team-supplied. Parents buy shoes, practice clothes, and a few small things.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Cheer shoes', body: [
        'White, low-profile, designed for stunting (not running). Specific brands by team.',
        'Sized to the foot. A snug fit is preferred for stunting.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Practice wear', body: [
        'Sized like athletic gear. Sports bra, leggings or shorts, a fitted t-shirt or tank.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Bow', body: [
        'The team usually orders one bow per season. Sized one-size-fits-all on a clip.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
