      ]},
    ],
  },
  dance: {
    intro: 'Dance shoes are sized differently than street shoes. The studio will tell you what to buy and what brand.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Ballet slippers', body: [
        'Canvas or leather. Sized 1-2 sizes smaller than street shoe.',
        'Full-sole for ages 4-7. Split-sole for ages 8+.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Tap shoes', body: [
        'Sized true to street shoe.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Jazz shoes', body: [
        'Sized 1 size smaller than street shoe.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Tights and leotards', body: [
        'Sized 4-6, 6-8, 8-10, etc. The studio specifies brand and color.',
      ]},
    ],
  },
  ballet: {
    intro: 'Ballet sizing is technical. The studio prescribes everything. We list the major fit decisions parents should expect.',
    sections: [
      { heading: 'Slippers', body: [
        'Canvas split-sole is the common entry from age 6+.',
        'Full-sole leather for ages 3-6.',
        'Sized 1 size smaller than street shoe. Snug from heel to toe.',
      ]},
      { heading: 'Pointe shoes', body: [
        'Only when the teacher says (typically age 11-12 with two years of pre-pointe technique).',
        'Fitted at a specialty store. Brand, size, width, vamp depth all matter.',
